.TH AGENTGUARD-CLASSIFY-COMMAND 1 "2026-06-30" "agentguard" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
agentguard-classify-command \- classify executable command words as JSON
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B agentguard-classify-command
.RB [ --json ]
.RB [ --json-lines ]
.RB [ -- ]
.RI [ command ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B agentguard-classify-command
emits conservative command facts from Bash-like command text. It is the public
API for consumers that need AgentGuard's command-word model without sourcing
private hook helpers.
.PP
With command arguments, the arguments are joined with spaces and classified as
one command text. With no command arguments, input is read from standard input.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --json
Accepted for explicitness; JSON is the default output format.
.TP
.B --json-lines
Read one command per input line and print one JSON object per line containing
the original input and its classified command records.
.TP
.B --
Stop option parsing.
.TP
.BR -h ", " --help
Show usage.
.SH OUTPUT
Normal output has this shape:
.PP
.RS
.nf
{"commands":[{"fragment":"...","command":"...","basename":"..."}]}
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B --json-lines
adds the original
.B input
field to each line.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Classification completed.
.TP
.B 2
Usage error.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR claude-session-name (1)
